---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import CopyBlock from '../components/CopyBlock.astro';
const GH = 'https://github.com/nuthatch-indexer/nuthatch';
---
<Layout
  path="/install"
  title="Install Nuthatch"
  description="Install Nuthatch: a one-line installer or prebuilt binaries for macOS (Apple Silicon) and Linux x86_64, or cargo install. The installer always fetches the latest release — v0.4.0 today, with v0.5.0 (the delightful core + agent-grade MCP) landing imminently. Checksums verified; a Homebrew tap, an OCI image, and release signatures are on the way."
>
  <section class="page">
    <div class="wrap narrow">
      <p class="section-label">Install</p>
      <h1>Get Nuthatch running.</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        Embedded mode is a single static binary with no external services. Pick whichever
        route you trust. Every one lands you at the same place: <code>nuthatch init</code>,
        then <code>nuthatch dev</code>.
      </p>

      <p class="prerelease-note">
        <strong>v0.5.0 is landing.</strong> It carries the delightful core (interactive
        <code>sql</code>, chain auto-detect, <code>add</code>) and the agent-grade MCP surface. The
        last published tag is <strong>v0.4.0</strong>; the one-line installer and <code>cargo</code>
        always fetch the latest release, so you'll get 0.5.0 the moment it publishes. Prebuilt
        binaries ship for macOS (Apple Silicon) and Linux x86_64. Nuthatch is early 0.x software under
        a config-stability contract - see the <a href="/roadmap">roadmap</a>. A Homebrew tap, an OCI
        image, and detached release signatures are still on the way; other platforms build from source
        with <code>cargo</code> for now.
      </p>

      <h2 class="ih">Shell script</h2>
      <p>Detects your platform, downloads the matching static binary from the latest GitHub release, verifies its SHA-256 checksum, and puts it on your <code>PATH</code>. Covers macOS Apple Silicon and Linux x86_64; other targets fall back to <code>cargo</code>.</p>
      <CopyBlock command="curl -fsSL https://nuthatch-indexer.com/install.sh | sh" size="lg" />
      <p class="note">
        Piping to a shell asks for trust. Read it first:
        <a href="https://github.com/nuthatch-indexer/nuthatch-frontend/blob/main/public/install.sh" rel="noopener">the script is short and on GitHub</a>,
        or download it, read it, then run it.
      </p>

      <h2 class="ih">Cargo</h2>
      <p>If you have a Rust toolchain (1.95 or newer), build from source off crates.io. No prebuilt binary in the trust path.</p>
      <CopyBlock command="cargo install nuthatch" />
      <p class="note">
        Or grab a tarball and its <code>.sha256</code> yourself from the
        <a href="https://github.com/nuthatch-indexer/nuthatch/releases/latest" rel="noopener">latest GitHub release</a>.
      </p>

      <h2 class="ih">Homebrew <span class="tag">planned</span></h2>
      <p>macOS and Linuxbrew, once a tap is published.</p>
      <CopyBlock command="brew install nuthatch" />

      <h2 class="ih">Docker - scaled mode <span class="tag">planned</span></h2>
      <p>
        Embedded mode needs no Docker. The compose stack is for scaled mode - where Postgres
        replaces the embedded hot store and DataFusion federates hot and cold behind one SQL
        surface. That mode, and this stack, are not built yet.
      </p>
      <CopyBlock command="curl -fsSL https://nuthatch-indexer.com/docker-compose.yml -o docker-compose.yml && docker compose up" prompt={true} />

      <h2 class="ih">First run</h2>
      <p>Point it at a contract and go. Public RPC defaults; no key required.</p>
      <CopyBlock command="nuthatch init 0xA0b86991c6218b36c1d19D4a2e9Eb0cE3606eB48 --chain mainnet" />
      <CopyBlock command="nuthatch dev" />
      <p class="note">
        <code>init</code> resolves each contract's ABI (proxies included), scaffolds a nest, and
        writes a <code>schema.json</code>, an <code>llms.txt</code>, and a Claude Code skill. Pass
        several addresses to index a multi-contract nest, and <code>--chain arbitrum-one</code> or
        <code>--chain base</code> for the L2s. <code>dev</code> follows the tip and serves
        <code>/tables</code>, <code>/table/{'{'}name{'}'}</code>, read-only <code>/sql</code>,
        balances, <code>/metrics</code>, and MCP on one local endpoint.
      </p>

      <hr class="divider ih-div" />

      <h2 class="ih">Verify what you downloaded</h2>
      <p>
        Every release binary ships with a SHA-256 checksum file. The shell script checks the sum for
        you; do it yourself for the manual download.
      </p>
      <CopyBlock command="sha256sum -c nuthatch-<target>.tar.gz.sha256" prompt={true} />
      <div class="keybox">
        <span class="keybox-label">Detached signatures <span class="tag">planned</span></span>
        <p class="keybox-note">
          Releases ship checksums but not yet detached signatures. Minisign and cosign signing, with a
          published key, land with the remaining release engineering - see the
          <a href="/roadmap">roadmap</a>. Until then, verify the checksum.
        </p>
      </div>

      <p class="backlink"><a href={GH} rel="noopener">Source, docs, and issues on GitHub →</a></p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .page { padding-block: clamp(3rem, 6vw, 4.5rem) clamp(4rem, 8vw, 6rem); }
  .page h1 { margin-bottom: 1.2rem; }
  .lede { color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 1.1rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .ih { margin-top: 2.8rem; margin-bottom: 0.8rem; font-size: 1.35rem; }
  .ih-div { margin-block: 2.8rem 0; }
  .page p { color: var(--text-muted); margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .page :global(.copyblock) { margin-bottom: 0.6rem; }
  .note { font-size: 0.88rem; color: var(--text-faint); }
  .prerelease-note {
    background: var(--pale-rust-bg); border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--rust); border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: 0.9rem 1.1rem; font-size: 0.92rem; margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  .ih .tag { font-size: 0.62rem; vertical-align: middle; margin-left: 0.4rem; }
  .keybox { margin-top: 1rem; background: var(--bg-elev); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: var(--radius); padding: 1.2rem 1.3rem; }
  .keybox-label { font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.7rem; letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--text-faint); }
  .keybox-id { display: block; margin-top: 0.5rem; font-size: 0.82rem; color: var(--accent-ink); word-break: break-all; }
  .keybox-note { margin: 0.6rem 0 0; font-size: 0.82rem; }
  .backlink { margin-top: 2.5rem; }
  .backlink a { font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.9rem; }
</style>
